Data Download

This sample notebook demonstrates how to programatically download and visualize air quality data stored on the Open Storage Network

# Parameters
test_parameter = 1.618
1.618

This is a sample markdown string

\[\begin{equation} \int_a^b f(x)dx \end{equation}\]

We can do equations!

Further, we can impute values. For example, the maximum PM 2.5 concentration for 5-2-2023 was 49.67306784 μg/m³

Let’s create a simple plot:

plot(
    date2datetime.(df_IPS7100.dateTime),
    df_IPS7100.pm2_5,
    ylabel="Concentration [μg/m³]",
    title="PM 2.5 at Central Node 8",
    lw=3,
    label="",
    xrotation=45,
    margin=10*Plots.mm,
    size=(900,650),
)

That plot looks great! Let’s now demonstrate the use of notebook parameters with papermill. In the first cell we define the variable test_parameter to the value 3.14. At execution time, the value is now 1.618
